# TypeScript + Next.js + Supabase

You are an expert in TypeScript, Node.js, Next.js App Router, React, Material UI, Supabase, Tailwind, TanStack Query, and Vercel AI SDK.

## Project paths

- App Router: `src/app` only — never create root-level `app/`
- Supabase clients: centralize in `src/lib/supabase` (or existing project location)
- Server actions: `src/actions` or colocated with routes

## Code style and structure

- Write concise, technical TypeScript with accurate examples
- Use functional and declarative patterns; avoid classes
- Prefer iteration and modularization over duplication
- Use descriptive names with auxiliary verbs (e.g., `isLoading`, `hasError`)
- Structure files: exported component, subcomponents, helpers, static content, types

## Naming conventions

- Lowercase with dashes for directories (e.g., `components/auth-wizard`)
- Favor named exports for components

## TypeScript

- TypeScript for all code; prefer interfaces over type aliases for objects
- Avoid enums; use const objects or `as const`
- Functional components with TypeScript interfaces

## UI and styling

- Primary UI: Material UI (MUI) per project stack
- Use Tailwind where the project already mixes utility classes
- Responsive, mobile-first layouts

## Supabase

- Use `@supabase/ssr` for server/client Supabase clients — not deprecated auth-helpers
- On the server, authenticate with `getUser()` — never rely on `getSession()` alone
- Enable Row Level Security on every table; define policies per operation
- Use generated Supabase types for query type safety
- Mutations: prefer Server Actions with Zod validation and `getUser()` checks

## Performance

- Minimize `'use client'`, `useEffect`, and `useState`; favor Server Components
- Wrap client components in `Suspense` with fallbacks
- Dynamic-import non-critical client components
- Optimize images with `next/image`

## Data fetching

- Server Components for initial data where possible
- TanStack Query for client-side cache/sync when appropriate
- Use Next.js caching and revalidation (`revalidatePath`, `revalidateTag`)
- Route handlers (`route.ts`) for webhooks and external API surfaces

## Vercel AI SDK

- Use for chat, streaming, and tool-calling features
- Keep provider keys server-side only
- Prefer RSC/streaming patterns aligned with App Router

## Error handling

- `error.tsx` boundaries for route segments that fetch data
- `loading.tsx` for async route loading states
- Return structured errors from Server Actions (success/error union)

## SEO and metadata

- Use the App Router `metadata` export or `generateMetadata` for pages

Follow official Next.js docs for data fetching, rendering, and routing.
